<subSubSection pageId="195" pageNumber="473" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="195.[726,1317,2037,2455]" pageId="195" pageNumber="473">
Morphological and karyological data suggest that A. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1894" box="[900,972,2151,2180]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Acodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="195" pageNumber="473" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mollis">mollis</taxonomicName>
likely represents a complex of several lowland and highland species. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
